Package: SpeedDada
Type: Package
Title: High-Performance Drop-In Replacement for DADA2 (Rust Core)
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Alexandre",
           family = "Jousset",
           email = "info@genedance.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person(given = "Genedance GmbH",
           role = "cph"))
Description: A drop-in replacement for the dada2 amplicon sequence variant
    (ASV) pipeline (Callahan et al. 2016, <doi:10.1038/nmeth.3869>),
    implemented in Rust and exposed via 'extendr'. Provides identical
    'filterAndTrim', 'learnErrors', 'derepFastq', 'dada', 'mergePairs',
    'makeSequenceTable', and 'removeBimeraDenovo' APIs, but typically
    one to two orders of magnitude faster and with roughly ten-fold
    lower peak memory through streaming dereplication, disk-backed
    pooling, and compact bitset taxonomy profiles. Builds with the
    user's Rust toolchain (rustup recommended) on Linux, macOS, and
    Windows, including aarch64/ARM (Raspberry Pi).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
